      • maybeQuestionAvailable

        boolean maybeQuestionAvailable(LookupRoot container,
                               java.util.Date referenceDate)
        True if the Question is available, false otherwise. This merely tests availability as defined by lookup tables and the availability script; it does not test it based on filtering.

      • isQuestionAvailable

        boolean isQuestionAvailable(AnswerContainer container)
        True if the Question is available, false otherwise. This merely tests availability as defined by lookup tables and the availability script; it does not test it based on filtering.

      • getReferenceDate

        java.util.Date getReferenceDate(AnswerContainer container)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        reference date to be used for availability lookups

      • isQuestionVisible

        boolean isQuestionVisible(AnswerContainer container)
        Returns true if the question is visible according to all its filters (or has none), false if at least one filter indicates that the question shouldn't be visible.
        Parameters:
        container - the AnswerContainer to evaluate the filters against
        Returns:
        true if the question is visible, false if it should be filtered out

      • getOrderedSupplementalTexts

        SupplementalText[] getOrderedSupplementalTexts()
        Returns the supplemental texts ordered first according to priority, then by text, an finally according to public id. This method will sort the supplemental texts each and every time they are pulled, so if you are worried about performance use the method getSupplementalTexts() instead.
        Returns:
        The supplemental texts for this question ordered by priority, text, and public id.
